'''Ordhelm''' was a son of [[Orodreth]] in the early versions of the [[legendarium]].<ref name=Ord>{{SM|QA1}}, p. 213</ref> Nothing else is known about him.

== Etymology ==
The name ''Ordhelm'' is in [[Old English]], since it was translated by [[Ælfwine]], but no [[Elvish]] equivalent is given.<ref name=Ord/> In modern English, this could mean "Spear-helm" ("ord" meaning "spear",<ref>[https://archive.org/details/anglosaxondictio00tolluoft/page/676/mode/1up ''An Anglo-Saxon dictionary : based on the manuscript collections of the late Joseph Bosworth. Supplement'', pg. 676]</ref> and "helm" carrying the same meaning<ref>[https://archive.org/details/anglosaxondictio00tolluoft/page/530/mode/2up ''An Anglo-Saxon dictionary : based on the manuscript collections of the late Joseph Bosworth. Supplement'', pg. 530]</ref>).

